</div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9f15" data-pf-type="Section" id="Cultivation" class="sc-fsvrPk eTuePL pf-150_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eNSrbD jPuwGZ"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-151_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-152_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau.png?v=1711454056 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_1000x.png?v=1711454056 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056 320w" width="3514" height="230" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Pflanzenstrich_blau.png__PID:b850d7e1-c00f-4273-9b83-e2ecbfbe7683" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-153_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-154_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-155_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenanbaukarte_web_500x.jpg?v=1713520828" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenanbaukarte_web.jpg?v=1713520828 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenanbaukarte_web_1000x.jpg?v=1713520828 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenanbaukarte_web_500x.jpg?v=1713520828 320w" width="2000" height="1000" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Rosenanbaukarte_web.jpg__PID:750d05b9-f363-4e0c-a2c3-cb6911469108" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-156_ pf-image-1"/><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-157_ pf-heading-1-h3">Damascena Rose Cultivation
</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-159_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-160_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-161_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-162_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Roseharvest_persia_500x.jpg?v=1713774462" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Roseharvest_persia.jpg?v=1713774462 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Roseharvest_persia_500x.jpg?v=1713774462 320w" width="780" height="370" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Roseharvest_persia.jpg__PID:cb691146-9108-4cba-a801-be4514cc585a" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-163_ pf-image-1"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-164_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-165_ pf-heading-1-h3">Iran / Persia<br></h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-167_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In Persia, the cradle of rose cultivation, the love affair with Rosa Damascena dates back thousands of years. It is believed that the Persians were among the first to recognize the transformative potential of distilling roses into essential oils. While the exact origins of rose distillation remain shrouded in the mists of time, it is clear that the Persians played a pivotal role in elevating this ancient art form to new heights. Despite the misconception that Ibn Senna (Avicenna) pioneered rose distillation in the 11th century, historical evidence suggests that the Persians were already distilling roses long before his time.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-169_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-170_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenernte_Bulgarien_500x.jpg?v=1713275329" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenernte_Bulgarien.jpg?v=1713275329 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenernte_Bulgarien_500x.jpg?v=1713275329 320w" width="789" height="370" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Rosenernte_Bulgarien.jpg__PID:7ef3ccd1-fcd2-4c94-af79-01b4b34d5d27" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-171_ pf-image-1"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-172_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-173_ pf-heading-1-h3">Bulgaria</h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-175_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Bulgaria, often hailed as the "Rose Valley" of the world, has earned international acclaim for its superior quality Rosa Damascena. Nestled amidst the rolling hills of the Balkans, the Bulgarian rose fields bloom with an abundance of fragrant blossoms, painting the landscape in hues of pink and red. Here, rose cultivation is not merely a profession but a cherished tradition passed down through generations. The Bulgarian people take great pride in their role as custodians of the Damask rose, employing time-honored methods to cultivate and harvest these precious blooms.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-177_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-178_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenernte_Turkey_500x.jpg?v=1713275495" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenernte_Turkey.jpg?v=1713275495 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenernte_Turkey_500x.jpg?v=1713275495 320w" width="796" height="370" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Rosenernte_Turkey.jpg__PID:ccd1fcd2-0c94-4f79-81b4-b34d5d27511d" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-179_ pf-image-1"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-180_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-181_ pf-heading-1-h3">Turkey</h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-183_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In Turkey, the land where East meets West, Rosa Damascena thrives amidst a landscape steeped in history and romance. Turkish rose cultivation is characterized by its meticulous attention to detail and unwavering commitment to quality. From the fertile soils of the Anatolian plateau to the sun-drenched fields of Isparta, Turkish roses flourish under the watchful gaze of skilled cultivators. The roses are harvested with reverence and care, their petals carefully gathered to preserve their delicate fragrance and therapeutic properties.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-185_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-186_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenfest_Marokko_500x.png?v=1713262879" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenfest_Marokko.png?v=1713262879 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Rosenfest_Marokko_500x.png?v=1713262879 320w" width="800" height="369" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Rosenfest_Marokko.png__PID:733a7ef3-ccd1-4cd2-8c94-af7901b4b34d" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-187_ pf-image-1"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-188_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-189_ pf-heading-1-h3">Morocco</h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-191_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Morocco, with its vibrant markets and bustling souks, is another bastion of Rosa Damascena cultivation. Here, amidst the labyrinthine streets of Marrakech and the sun-drenched valleys of the Atlas Mountains, the Damask rose reigns supreme. Moroccan rose oil, known for its rich aroma and amber hue, is prized by perfumers and aromatherapists alike. The cultivation of roses in Morocco is a labor of love, with farmers tending to their fields with dedication and devotion.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-193_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" id="Video2" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-194_"><div data-pf-type="Youtube" class="sc-campCi fJvUhn pf-195_"><div style="position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;border-radius:inherit"><iframe class="pf-ifr" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0aDzfXjd8ro?start=0&autoplay=0&loop=0&mute=0&controls=0&enablejsapi=1" allowfullscreen="" width="560" height="315" allow="autoplay" title="yt-video" loading="lazy" style="border-radius:inherit"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-8f5d" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fsvrPk eTuePL pf-196_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eNSrbD jPuwGZ"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-197_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-198_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau.png?v=1711454056 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_1000x.png?v=1711454056 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056 320w" width="3514" height="230" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Pflanzenstrich_blau.png__PID:b850d7e1-c00f-4273-9b83-e2ecbfbe7683" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-199_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-200_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-201_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/rose_closeup_500x.jpg?v=1712239033" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/rose_closeup.jpg?v=1712239033 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/rose_closeup_1000x.jpg?v=1712239033 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/rose_closeup_500x.jpg?v=1712239033 320w" width="2000" height="1055" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="rose_closeup.jpg__PID:15ee862a-2497-49eb-8f35-70b7c3632acc" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-202_ pf-image-1"/><h1 data-pf-type="Heading2" id="Compounds" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-203_ pf-heading-1-h3">All you can have: Rose Essential Oil&nbsp;consists of more than 500 compounds</h1><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-205_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-206_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-207_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The essence of Rosa Damascena, captured within its precious oil, is a veritable treasure trove of healing potentials, boasting over 500 different compounds, each with its own unique virtues and therapeutic properties. The major ones are: Citronellol, Citral, Carvone, Citronellyl acetate, Eugenol, Ethanol, Farsenol, Stearpoten, Methyl eugenol, Nerol, Nonanol, Nonanal, Phenyl acetaldehyde, Phenylmenthyl acetate and Phenyl geraniol. <br>Yet, amidst this abundance lies a realm of mystery and intrigue, as the majority of nature's bio-molecules remain unexplored and enigmatic, their profound healing virtues and hidden psycho-spiritual effects waiting to be unveiled. While modern science has made significant strides in analyzing and understanding some of the compounds found within Rosa Damascena oil, there is still much to discover. Many of nature's bio-molecules have yet to be fully comprehended in terms of their multifaceted healing </p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-209_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-210_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">capabilities, let alone their intricate synergistic interactions with one another. Indeed, the healing potential of Rosa Damascena oil extends far beyond the realm of physical well-being, reaching into the depths of the mind and soul. Each compound within the oil carries with it a subtle energy and resonance, capable of eliciting profound shifts in consciousness and emotional states. <br>These psycho-spiritual "side-effects" are often subtle and nuanced, yet their impact can be profound, offering a pathway to inner transformation. As we continue to explore the depths of nature's wisdom, we are reminded of the inherent complexity and beauty of the natural world. Within the petals of Rosa Damascena lies a wealth of healing potentials waiting to be discovered, offering a glimpse into the infinite mysteries of the universe and the profound interconnectedness of all life.</p></div></div></div><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-212_ pf-heading-1-h3"><em>"More than 500 different compounds – each of them a superlative in itself of specific healing impulses for our body, mind and soul."</em></h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-214_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">DR. MALTE HOZZEL ON ROSA DAMASCENA ESSENTIAL OIL<br></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-114b" data-pf-type="Section" id="Meaning" class="sc-fsvrPk eTuePL pf-216_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eNSrbD jPuwGZ"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-217_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-218_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau.png?v=1711454056 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_1000x.png?v=1711454056 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056 320w" width="3514" height="230" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Pflanzenstrich_blau.png__PID:b850d7e1-c00f-4273-9b83-e2ecbfbe7683" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-219_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-220_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-221_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-222_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The different colors of the flower represent different qualities and emotions:</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-224_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-md:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-225_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/rosen_verschiedene_farben_310x.jpg?v=1712146155" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/rosen_verschiedene_farben.jpg?v=1712146155 1536w" width="800" height="533" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="rosen_verschiedene_farben.jpg__PID:e5053587-5f25-47a0-bb05-4c77bfb6401f" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-knuQPt boqfLv pf-226_ pf-image-1"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:8;--c-md:8;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-227_"><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dhFVuh gFqzWs pf-228_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fbKhWw bnrVBh pf-229_ pf-text-1">Red Rose stands for love, passion, respect and courage.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fbKhWw bnrVBh pf-231_ pf-text-1">White Rose describes innocence, purity and secrecy.
